# See https://help.github.com/articles/ignoring-files for more about ignoring files.
#
# If you find yourself ignoring temporary files generated by your text editor
# or operating system, you probably want to add a global ignore instead:
#   git config --global core.excludesfile '~/.gitignore_global'

# Ignore bundler config.
/.bundle

# Ignore the default SQLite database.
/db/*.sqlite3
/db/*.sqlite3-journal

# Ignore all logfiles and tempfiles.
/log/*
/tmp/*
!/log/.keep
!/tmp/.keep

# Ignore uploaded files in development
/storage/*
!/storage/.keep

/node_modules
/yarn-error.log

/public/assets
.byebug_history

# Ignore master key for decrypting credentials and more.
/config/master.key
/public/packs
/public/packs-test
yarn-debug.log*

### Additional Ignoring Items
## JetBrains: covers RubyMine and IntelliJ IDEA (with Ruby plugin)
# References:
# - https://intellij-support.jetbrains.com/hc/en-us/articles/206544839
# - https://github.com/github/gitignore/blob/master/Global/JetBrains.gitignore
/.idea/*

# .iml module files, which are recommended to add
!/.idea/modules.xml
!/*.iml

# Shared configurations (Run/Debug configurations with 'Share' checked)
!/.idea/runConfigurations/

# Make it easier to import data sources
!/.idea/dataSources.xml

# Encoding settings
!/.idea/encodings.xml

# For better use of spell checker (except 'dictionaries' dir, ignore all files under it except some user-specific setting files)
!.idea/dictionaries/
.idea/dictionaries/*
!.idea/dictionaries/user-name.xml

# Others
!/.idea/vcs.xml

## JetBrains Plugins
# Railways
/railways.cache

## Gems
# rails-erd gem
/erd.pdf

# Webpacker/JavaScript
.yarn-integrity

